Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "kolače" in different forms and positions:

1. *Kolače* sam danas pekla sa mamom. (I baked *cakes* today with my mom.)
2. Mmm, ove *kolače* sam probala pre nekoliko dana i bili su fantastični. (Mmm, I tried these *cakes* a few days ago and they were fantastic.)
3. Kada pravim *kolače*, uvek koristim brašno koje samleti moj deda u svojoj mlinici. (When I make *cakes*, I always use flour that my grandfather ground in his mill.)
4. Na slavu smo kupili mnogo *kolača*, pa smo ih delili svim gostima. (For the celebration, we bought a lot of *cakes*, and we shared them with all the guests.)
5. *Kolače* su mi omiljena poslastica, ali ne jedem ih često jer pokušavam da vodim zdrav životni stil. ( *Cakes* are my favorite dessert, but I don't eat them often because I'm trying to lead a healthy lifestyle.)
6. Zamolila bih te da mi pomogneš da dekorišem ove *kolače*. (I would like to ask you to help me decorate these *cakes*.)
7. *Kolači* koje si napravio su izvanredni! (The *cakes* you made are outstanding!)
8. Na rođendanu smo jeli mnogo različitih vrsta *kolača*. (At the birthday party, we ate a lot of different kinds of *cakes*.)
9. Kada sam bila mala, često sam pravila male lutkice od testa dok su *kolači* bili u rerni. (When I was little, I used to make small dough dolls while the *cakes* were baking in the oven.)
10. Kad god idem u poslastičarnicu, uvek naručim različite vrste *kolača* da probam. (Whenever I go to a pastry shop, I always order different types of *cakes* to try.)

Note: In the examples above, the word "kolače" is highlighted with an asterisk (*) for easier identification.